{"title_page": "Sandy Denny discography", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist discography\n|Artist       = [[Sandy Denny]]\n|Image        = \n|Image size   = \n|Caption      = \n|Studio       = 4\n|Live         = 2\n|Soundtrack   = \n|Compilation  = 15\n|EP           = 1\n|Singles      = 4\n|Music videos = \n|Option       = 2\n|Option name  = Collaborations\n}}\n\nThe '''Sandy Denny discography''' chronicles the output of British [[folk rock]] singer [[Sandy Denny]].  Her brief career, spanning 1967 to 1978, saw the release of 4 solo albums and 4 singles on several record labels.\n\nDenny was the lead singer of the group [[Fairport Convention]], and fronted the band through several of their most highly regarded albums: ''[[What We Did on Our Holidays]]'', ''[[Unhalfbricking]]'', and ''[[Liege & Lief]]'' were all released by the band during 1969, and are today considered touchstones in the progression of British folk rock. Fairport guitarist and songwriter [[Richard Thompson (musician)|Richard Thompson]] would prove to be an important collaborator in Denny's life, and he would go on to perform guitar duties on each of her solo albums. \n\nIn addition to her work with Fairport Convention, Denny was also a member of [[The Strawbs]], [[Fotheringay]] and [[The Bunch]]. Other notable recordings include her duet with [[Robert Plant]] on [[Led Zeppelin]]'s \"The Battle of Evermore\", as well as a brief appearance on a live version of [[The Who]]'s ''[[Tommy (London Symphony Orchestra album)|Tommy]]''. She has received a number of awards and accolades from different organizations.\n\n==Solo==\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|Year\n!align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|Album\n!align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|[[UK Albums Chart]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1971\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''[[The North Star Grassman and the Ravens]]''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|31\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1972\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''[[Sandy (Sandy Denny album)|Sandy]]''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1974\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''[[Like an Old Fashioned Waltz]]''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1977\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''[[Rendezvous (Sandy Denny album)|Rendezvous]]''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|}\n\n===Live albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|Year\n!align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|Album\n!align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|[[UK Albums Chart]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1998\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''[[Gold Dust (Sandy Denny album)|Gold Dust]]''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|2011\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''19 Rupert Street''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|}\n\n===Compilation albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|Year\n!align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|Album\n!align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"40\"|[[UK Albums Chart]]\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1970\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''[[It's Sandy Denny]]''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1985\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''[[Who Knows Where the Time Goes? (Sandy Denny album)|Who Knows Where the Time Goes?]]''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1987\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''The Best of Sandy Denny''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1995\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''The Attic Tracks 1972-1984''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|1999\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''Listen Listen - An Introduction to Sandy Denny''\n|align=\"center\" valign=\"top\"|-\n|-\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|2000\n|align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"|''No More Sad Refrains: The Anthology''\